7.01	Nakh_peoples	Nakh peoples	Nakh peoples are a group of historical and modern ethnic groups speaking (or historically speaking) Nakh languages and sharing certain cultural traits. In modern days, they reside almost completely in the North Caucasus, but historically large areas of the South Caucasus may have also been Nakh.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Chechense._Match._a_wedding_match._George_Kennan._1870-1886.jpg/250px-Chechense._Match._a_wedding_match._George_Kennan._1870-1886.jpg
